                  <handDesc>
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">19th – early 20th-century script; fine, but not very regular hand. <note>
                           <p>Unknown</p>
                           
                        </note>
                        <note>
                           <p>- In order to accommodate longer text lines, the scribe employed compressed script, fols. <locus target="#2r"/>
                              <locus from="6r"/>v, <locus target="#7r #8r"/>
                              <locus from="10r"/>v, <locus from="11r"/>v, <locus target="#12r #13v"/>etc., frequently in combination with runovers marked with red and/or black lines, fols. <locus target="#6r #12r #13v #21r #30v #79v"/>
                           </p>
                           <p>- Ps. <locus target="#118"/>:<locus target="#116"/>is placed in a “net” made of red lines, fol. <locus target="#85v"/>
                           </p>
                           <p>- Mistaken words are cancelled with red lines, fol. <locus target="#85v"/>
                           </p>
                           <p>- Midpoint of the Psalms is marked on fol. <locus target="#50v"/>.  </p>
                        </note>
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                          Executed in the main hand.
                           
                        </seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="other" xml:id="d2">
                       
                        <p>- Decorated quire marks are written in the top left corner of the first leaf of each quire. </p>
                        <p>- Coloured threads are inserted in one of the upper pricks: yellow in fol. <locus target="#27"/>; red in fols. <locus target="#55 #66"/>; violet in fols. <locus target="#77 #87 #94"/>.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                     <decoNote type="mixed" xml:id="d3">
                        <p>Each unit of ten Psalms and other texts are preceded by an elaborate polychrome ornamental band, in the top margin of fols. <locus target="#1r #6v #12v #19r #27r #33r #38r #45v #55r #62r #66v #77r #87r #89v #94v #100r #110v #116r"/>.</p>
                        
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <p>I) Fol. <locus target="#1r"/>:ፍካሬ፡ዘጻድቃን፡ወዘኃጥአን።ተግሣጽ፡ለኵሉ።</p>
                           <p>መዝሙር፡ዘዳዊት፡ሃሊ፡ሉያ።</p>
                           <p>ብፁዕ፡ብእሲ፡ዘኢሖረ፡በምክረ፡ረሢዓን፨</p>
                           <p>ወዘኢቆመ፡ውስተ፡ፍኖተ፡ኃጥአን፨</p>
                           
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="true">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">
                           <p>Ethiopian binding. Two wooden boards, light-brown cotton secondary cover with a tongue protecting the edges of the volume. </p>
                           <p>Two pair of sewing stations.</p>
                           <p>Kept in the traditional two-part slip leather case (worn, the leather strap is missing). </p>
                           
                        </decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
